title: $59 million Bunnings warehouse at Gungahlin is now under construction
text:
Under construction: Gungahlin is getting its own Bunnings. Photo: Glenn Hunt
A $59 million Bunnings Warehouse is under construction in Gungahlin, further confirming that Canberra's northern reaches are growing at a rapid pace.
Bunnings general manager of property Andrew Marks said the 17,000 square metre outlet was taking shape on the corner of Gribble and Hibberson streets.
The development will include a main warehouse, an indoor timber trade sales area, a building materials and landscape supplies yard and an outdoor nursery.
There will also be an indoor playground and cafe. The development includes parking for 420 cars.
Advertisement Mr Marks said once opened, the warehouse would provide 180 jobs.
He said an additional 520 jobs were being created during the construction process.
"Construction of the new warehouse is currently underway with all earthworks, external concrete slabs and wall panels in place," Mr Marks said.
"The warehouse steelworks and roof are in progress with external roadworks to commence soon."
ADCO Construction has been appointed to complete the project.
The development also included a number of energy and water-saving design features.
Those included rainwater tanks to irrigate the nursery, LED lighting and a solar-boosted hot water system.
The development is expected to be completed by the end of the year.
